  "@id": "https://figshare.com/articles/dataset/GRUN_Global_Runoff_Reconstruction/9228176#dataset",
  "name": "G-RUN (GRUN): Global Runoff Reconstruction",
  "url": "https://figshare.com/articles/dataset/GRUN_Global_Runoff_Reconstruction/9228176",
  "description": "GRUN (Global Runoff Reconstruction; often referred to as G-RUN) is an observation-based global gridded reconstruction of monthly runoff derived using machine learning trained on in-situ streamflow observations. The dataset provides global runoff rates on a 0.5° grid over the period 1902–2014 and is intended for analyses of freshwater dynamics, hydroclimate variability, drought propagation, and evaluation of hydrological model simulations.",
